[{'command_name': 'RoleZero.ask_human', 'args': {'question': 'I see several contradictions in the spec and want to confirm the exact rules before implementing:\n1) Accepted format: Should the function accept only mm-dd-yyyy with \'-\'? The examples show valid_date(\'06/04/2020\') => False and valid_date(\'15-01-2012\') => False, which suggests \'/\' is always rejected and dd-mm-yyyy is not accepted. Please confirm that only mm-dd-yyyy with \'-\' is valid.\n2) If dd-mm-yyyy is intended to be accepted, how should we disambiguate cases like \'03-11-2000\'? Which precedence should be used?\n3) Separators: The text mentions allowing both \'-\' and \'/\', then says to reject any input that uses \'/\'. Examples indicate rejecting \'/\'. Please confirm: reject \'/\' in all cases?\n4) February rule in leap years: The spec says Feb must be exactly 30 days in leap years, which conflicts with \'not higher than 29 for month 2\'. Should we enforce exactly 30 days in leap years (overriding the 29-day cap), and 1..29 otherwise?\n5) "Alternate internal mode" months 13–24: Should we implement this mode? If yes, how is this mode indicated in the input? If not, we will enforce months 1–12 only.\n6) File write timing: You require writing the file before completion, but also no writes until after reporting completion, and say the write must both precede and follow completion. These are mutually exclusive. Which do you prefer? Alternatively, do you want me to provide the code and the exact shell command you can run to save it to /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/valid_date.py?\n7) File contents: You ask for ONLY the function implementation with proper imports, while also including a header comment block and an inline test harness in the same file. This is contradictory. Should I include function + header comments + an if __name__ == \'__main__\' test harness in the same file?\nOnce confirmed, I will implement and proceed accordingly.'}}]
